text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus dysophylla is a Mexican species of oak tree in the beech family. It grows in central Mexico in Hidalgo, México State, D.F., Puebla, Michoacán, and San Luis Potosí.Quercus dysophylla is a tree up to 20 meters tall. Leaves are thick and leathery, up to 17 cm long, elliptical with no teeth or lobes.
